Hyatt Says Middle East’s Hotel Market Starting to Recover

-- B y   S u s a n   L i
-- 
2011-10-12T03:44:51Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-10-12/hyatt-says-middle-east-s-hotel-market-starting-to-recover.html
Hyatt Hotels Corp. (H) , the chain
controlled by the Pritzker family, said the Middle East
hospitality market has started to recover.  Growth in  China  and  India  has been “relatively healthy,”
President and Chief Executive Officer Mark Hoplamazian said
today in a Bloomberg Television interview in  Hong Kong .  To contact the reporter on this story:
Susan Li in Hong Kong at 
